definitions.definition: An administration ( a body that administers; the executive part of government ) .
The administrative or managerial body of a company or other organization.
An administrator ( one who administers affairs ) .
A systems administrator ( one who maintains a computer system or network ) .
examples: Our admin has upgraded the server in our office, so we can exchange files faster.

definitions.definition: A user of a discussion forum , website , etc. with privileges allowing them to control or restrict the activity of other users.
examples: The admin changed the forum settings to enable the use of emoticons.
